reviewText: High quality as always expected from the Perry Mason body of work.

I like all of the Perry Mason shows.  But these latter versions seem to be even better.  Perry has aged, Della has
aged...The plots seem more involved, and somewhat smoother-if there is such a thing.  Good stuff.
Perry's movies are awesome.  We enjoy them.  We have seen them, but wanted them in DVD instead of VHS.
Love Perry Mason mysteries.  Hope to complete my collection soon.  I used to read the Books  and now I'm happy to have them on DVD.
This was to complete our collection.
Perry Mason and Della Street never get too old to do this stuff.
See my other reviews on the later movies: it's great Perry Mason.
I love Raymond Burr and ALL of his shows, movies he has done. One of my favorites is  The Case of The Maligned Mobster is because my favortite singer is in this movie. He is Paul Anka.
